# Models, Parsing & Ingestion

## Module split

| Module | Role |
|--------|------|
| `models.py` | Pydantic schemas (`Collar`, `Lithology`, `ParseResult`, `ConsultingTitleBlock`, …) + compat re-exports |
| `parsing.py` | `DataParser` and Excel sheet parsers |
| `parse_ops.py` | `subset_parse_result`, `apply_unit_order_fix`, `geology_sheet_counts`, lithology index helpers |
| `ingestion.py` | `FormatDetector`, `FieldExportAdapter`, `ingest_workbook()` |
| `workbook_template.py` | Multi-tab input template builder + Data Entry helpers (no geometry) |

Prefer `from models import DataParser, subset_parse_result` (re-exports) or import from `parsing` / `parse_ops` directly. New parse logic goes in `parsing` / `parse_ops`, not `models.py`.

## Core schemas

```python
# Collar — hole_id, easting, northing, elevation, total_depth
# Lithology — hole_id, from_depth, to_depth, lithology_code, unit_order?
# WaterLevel — hole_id + depth (model always stores depth). Sheet input: depth XOR elevation_masl
#   (parser converts elevation_masl → depth via collar RL). Optional: series_id, series_label, color, marker
# ScreenInterval — hole_id, from_depth, to_depth
# VerticalGradient — hole_id, direction (up/down)
# ParseResult — collars, lithologies, errors, water_levels, screen_intervals, vertical_gradients, ...
```

Optional sheets: Water, Screens, Gradients, Deviations, Correlations, Faults, Unconformities, Environmental.
See `docs/workbook-format.md`. Template: `python scripts/build_input_template.py`.

### Parse error policy

| Sheet | Bad / unknown `hole_id` rows |
|-------|------------------------------|
| Collars, Lithology, Water, Screens, Gradients, Environmental | Append to `ParseResult.errors` (row kept only if valid) |
| Deviations, Correlations, Faults, Unconformities | Log-and-skip (not folded into `errors` today) |

Import profile `extends` chains are depth-capped and cycle-checked in `ingestion.py`.

## Boundaries

- No stratigraphy or projection logic in models/parsing/template
- Ingestion may call `ai_quality` for aliases and QA after parse
